@node "history" "SOPE - History"

 v000301 -000308
         -After about 50-60 hours of tracing endian related bugs, the big endian support in
          SOPE is starting to shape up real nicely.
         -All AmigaOS code (except OpenGL/Sound) is implemented and works.

 v000310 -000309
         -Now, this is strange, but with all timezones and stuff I can actually work on the
          10th of Mars release when it's still the 9th of Mars.
         -More endian fixes, now the TRex demo acts like it should, not that I get any gfx,
          but it wont stop with an error atleast.
         -Changed the way some of the variables are handled, should be a bit faster.
         -000311
         -After testing most demos I have and not finding any big problems (except for the
          Manta demo on the first playstation demo cd, which appears to end up in an infinitiv
          loop), I've decided to make a new release.

 v000418 -000319
         -Started writing a dynarec for SOPE, currently only a few instructions are emulated
          but most of the compiler has been written.
         -000320-000323
         -Added several instructions to the dynarec, improved the compiler a lot.
         -000324
         -Implemented more instructions.
         -Removed a bug related to all branch instructions.
         -000325
         -More instructions added, now GTE works (but slowly).
         -Fixed a bug with the SLT instructions which could get SOPE into an infinit loop.
         -Added the last instructions. The compatibility appears to be the same for the
          interpretive and dynaimc CPU core. The speed of the dynarec is sadly quite poor
          MAD1ST gives 10.5fps with interpreter and 20.9fps with dynarec (with the rendering
          disabled) on my 603e'200. There are a lot of places where optimization can be done
          however, so I hope to be able to improve things.
         -000327
         -Optimized the SLT instructions.
         -The compiled code now only push/pop the required registers, MAD1ST now gives 22.8fps.
         -Some minor changes to the compiler.
         -Optimized all GTE calls from the dynarec.
         -000328
         -Started working on a MiniGL version, but currently it just crashes.
         -Tried to compile a StormMESA version, but it don't work as supposed to currently.
         -000329
         -Modified the interpretive core to work with the changes done for the dynarec one.
         -Optimized the interpretive core somewhat, about 5-10% faster now.
         -General code cleanup.
         -000404
         -After a few days and many headaches, I've finally gotten the MiniGL version to work!
          Sadly there is no texture support in the OpenGL code from SOPE.
         -Of some reason, I have to compile MiniGL and SOPE with EGCS 2.95.1 to get MiniGL to
          work, and somehow this wrecks my dynarec a bit, the MAD1ST logo appears on the wrong
          place for example. I have NO idea about why currently. It's not possible to compile
          the GPU code with optimization either.
         -000405
         -Upgraded to EGCS 2.95.2 which appears to be less buggy (I can now compile the GPU
          code with optimization).
         -Fixed the dynarec bug. With EGCS 2.95.2 the arguments passed to the memwrite functions
          weren't masked as when compiling with GCC 2.7.2.1 which gave the strange result.
         -Minor changes to the dynarec and some GTE commands.
         -000411
         -Added a nice texture cache to the MiniGL renderer. There are some problems with
          the alignment which has to be fixed.
         -Made it possible for the renderer to disable ALL stdio, which is required unless
          one like to crash the Amiga while using MiniGL.
         -000413
         -Fixed the alignment problems with textures.
         -Added a custom GPU cache system since MiniGL doesn't support GL lists, of some
          reason this wrecks the MAD1ST logo, but the other demos I've tried do work ok,
          and if I disable the texture cache (reducing the speed from 26fps to 1fps), it
          looks weird at first, but it fixed itself. I have to investigate this.
         -000414
         -I don't seam to be able to fix the MAD1ST problem, I probably need to support the
          texture cache flush of the PSX for this to work correctly.
         -Just tried dynarec + MiniGL and got about 30fps in demos giving only 7-8fps using
          interpreter + software. A nice improvement :)
         -000418
         -Fixed the MAD1ST texture problem by caching the textures when they should've been
          used, and not when actually being used (i.e. while executing the cached GPU commands).

 v000502 -000501
         -Improved the output from the MiniGL version somewhat. Atleast the transparent areas
          of textures are transparent now. It's however impossible to get accurate output since
          no 3D hardware for the Amiga supports the required blendingmodes.
         -000502
         -changed the source layout somewhat. The makefile has been changed to always build all
          four versions of SOPE.


@endnode
